result.execSummary:
All charges against Angela Danielle Bossenbroek in this case have been dismissed. These charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Angela Danielle Bossenbroek is presumed innocent.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

8:28 AM Defendant Angela Danielle Bossenbroek in court.  Attorney Leonie Dolch in court for Angela Danielle Bossenbroek.  Attorney Natalia J Gess in court for State Of  Wisconsin.  State advises she spoke with the prosecutor in Texas and Texas is still pursuing the extradition.  They are in the process of securing the Governor's warrant.  Atty Dolch objects to an extension to allow Texas to complete the Governor's warrant.  Court notes at this point the State has not asked for an extension.  State does in fact ask for a 60 day extension.  Atty Dolch responds.  Court does not grant the request for an extension and after August 27, 2022, in the Court's opinion, this matter will no longer exist.  Atty Dolch requests matter be dismissed if no Governor's warrant is received by August 27, 2022.  That matter will be addressed at the TSC.
